# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# /api/demo (live "try with your own prompt" agent) routes through Vercel AI
# Gateway: streamText({ model: "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6", ... }).
# On a Vercel deployment with gateway access (most teams have it), nothing is
# needed, auth is auto-injected. Locally, `vercel link` + `vercel env pull`.
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AUDIT LOG + EL AUDITOR (the paid product). REQUIRED IN PRODUCTION.
# Missing any of these does NOT throw, it silently degrades, which for a paid
# "durable, signed, verifiable" product means selling something that isn't. If
# you set MERCADOPAGO_ACCESS_TOKEN (i.e. you are charging), you MUST also set
# KV + AUDIT_HMAC_SECRET or the audit log is neither durable nor signed.

# Vercel KV (Upstash). Without these, audit entries + entitlements go to an
# in-memory map that dies on cold start. REQUIRED for durability.
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=

# HMAC signing secret. Without it, entries are written with hmac:null and the
# "tamper-evident" promise is a no-op. REQUIRED. Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
# AUDIT_HMAC_SECRET=

# Ed25519 asymmetric signing (RFC-005). Additive, enables offline verification
# against the public key at /.well-known/sociedad-ia/keys.
# AUDIT_ED25519_PRIVATE_KEY=   # PKCS8 DER, base64url
# AUDIT_ED25519_PUBLIC_KEY=    # SPKI DER, base64url
# AUDIT_ED25519_KEY_ID=ar-agents-ref-2026-05

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MERCADO PAGO (El Auditor billing). Without MERCADOPAGO_ACCESS_TOKEN the
# subscribe endpoint runs in "early access" mode (no charge).
# MERCADOPAGO_ACCESS_TOKEN=    # APP_USR-... (production) to charge real money
# MERCADOPAGO_WEBHOOK_SECRET=  # verifies x-signature on /api/auditor/webhook
# AUDITOR_BACK_URL=            # defaults to https://ar-agents.ar/auditor/gracias
# AUDITOR_WEBHOOK_URL=         # defaults to https://ar-agents.ar/api/auditor/webhook

# ARS peg. Public price is USD 199/mo (1990/yr); MP settles in ARS. These env
# vars set the ARS amount so the peg tracks the USD price WITHOUT a redeploy.
# REVIEW THESE PERIODICALLY: a stale peg undercharges every NEW subscriber, and
# existing preapprovals keep their original ARS amount until updated in MP.
# Defaults (if unset): 249000 / 2490000 ARS.
# AUDITOR_PRICE_ARS_MENSUAL=249000
# AUDITOR_PRICE_ARS_ANUAL=2490000

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cron protection. If set, /api/auto-monitor requires it; if UNSET the route
# refuses to run (fail-closed) so it can't be triggered by anyone.
# CRON_SECRET=

# Higher GitHub API rate limit for /api/stats (optional).
# GITHUB_TOKEN=
